Huawei launched its new Kunpeng server boards at Huawei Connect 2019 in Shanghai, China. According to Huawei, the new Kunpeng server board offers up to 25% additional performance, 15% increased reliability, and energy efficiency improvements of up to 15% compared to industry competitors. “These boards will empower partners to built the ultimate computing products,” said Huawei’s president of its Intelligent Computing Business Department, Michael Ma. Huawei also announced a lineup of new Atlas server products that are powered by its Ascend 910 AI server chip. These include the Atlas 300, 800, and 900 products, each of which is detailed below. Bradley Prior is a guest of Huawei at Huawei Connect in China.